'''High comedy''' or '''pure comedy''' is a type of [[comedy]] characterized by [[wit]]ty dialogue, [[satire]], biting humor, or criticism of life.<ref>{{cite web|last=Trumbull |first=Eric W.|url=http://novaonline.nvcc.edu/eli/spd130et/typecomd.htm |title=Types of Drama / Plays: Comedy |publisher=Northern Virginia Community College |date=2008-01-04 |accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref>

Today, high comedy can be seen among [[sitcom]]s and [[talk shows]] targeted at cultured and articulate audiences. Examples of high comedy include [[Arrested Development (TV series)]], [[The Simpsons]], [[The Marx Brothers]], [[Woody Allen]], [[Seinfeld]], [[The Larry Sanders Show]] and [[The Office (UK TV series)]].

